"title": "6245: stubbornness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6245: stubbornness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Proud and disobedient resistance to God's will and rejection of his commands.</p>\n<h2>Stubbornness is an attitude of heart</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:24\">JER 7:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:27\">DEU 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:19\">JDG 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:8\">PSA 78:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:4\">ISA 48:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:17\">JER 3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:3\">JER 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:14\">JER 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:12\">JER 16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:12\">JER 18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:16\">HOS 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:11\">ZEC 7:11</a></p>\n<h2>The practical consequences of stubbornness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18\">EPH 4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:15\">EXO 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:3\">EXO 33:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:19\">LEV 26:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16\">2CH 26:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:16-Neh9:17\">NEH 9:16–9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:6-Job20:7\">JOB 20:6–20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:4\">PSA 10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:24-Prov1:31\">PRO 1:24–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:14\">PRO 28:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:1\">PRO 29:1</a> <em>sudden destruction for the unrepentant</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:11\">ISA 2:11</a> <em>a humbling on judgment day</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:3\">JER 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:8\">JER 11:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:10\">JER 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:20\">DAN 5:20</a> <em>King Nebuchadnezzar deposed</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:6\">HOS 13:6</a> <em>The people of Israel forget their God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:11\">ZEP 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:51-Mark6:52\">MRK 6:51–6:52</a> <em>Jesus Christ's disciples amazed</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:17\">MAT 18:15–18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a> <em>The self-righteous store up wrath for the day of judgment.</em></p>\n<h2>Commands not to be stubborn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:29\">NEH 9:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:5\">EXO 33:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:8\">2CH 30:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:8\">PSA 95:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:14\">MRK 16:14</a></p>\n<h2>Stubbornness can be God's judgment on sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:17\">ISA 63:17</a></strong> <em>When people persistently refuse to obey God, he brings about a condition where they cannot obey him, and consequently cannot receive his blessing.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:21\">EXO 4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:17\">EXO 14:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut2:30\">DEU 2:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:20\">JOS 11:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:11-Ps81:12\">PSA 81:11–81:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:18\">ROM 9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:7-Rom11:8\">ROM 11:7–11:8</a></p>\n<h2>God's appeal to stubborn people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:2\">ISA 65:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:21\">ROM 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:24-2Chr32:25\">2CH 32:24–32:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:16-Job33:18\">JOB 33:16–33:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:12\">ISA 46:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:22-Jer7:24\">JER 7:22–7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:4-Ezek2:5\">EZK 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:11-Zech7:12\">ZEC 7:11–7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8-Acts19:9\">ACT 19:8–19:9</a></p>",
